Field.FormMenuDescription: NCI Adverse Event Serious Adverse Event CTCAE V4 3265657v3 0

ElementEnum.RawValue:
1,Mild Adverse Event 
 2,Moderate Adverse Event 
 3,Severe Adverse Event 
 4,Life Threatening Adverse Event 
 5,Death Related to Adverse Event

Field.ElementNote: A coded value to identify the severity of the AE.

Date on which the AE was first evident. Conditionality Rule: Condition is that this is based on the needs of the Sponsor. CTEP does not currently collect Adverse Event onset dates for routine AEs reported via reporting systems.

Normally required only if AE is deemed 'serious'. Conditionality Rule: Conditional based on the reporting of this variable through other means, such as caAERS, AdEERS. If those systems are not in use, this variable needs to be collected.
A repeating period of activity involving treatment and rest. Several cycles can make up a course. Conditionality Rule: Studies use cycles.

Field.ElementLabel: To what is the AE attributed?
